---
title: Mustard Pork Chops with Green Beans & Crispy Potato Cakes
description: A mustard-shallot pan sauce takes these pork chops from delicious to company-worthy. Wringing out the potatoes is the secret to super crispy potato cakes - if you ever made latkes or hashbrowns, you know the drill. Don't forget to season your potato cakes while they're still hot!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/552e7f456ced6e3e4f8b4567.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/552e7f456ced6e3e4f8b4567.pdf
course: main course
time required: 45 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mustard-pork-chops-552e7f456ced6e3e4f8b4567
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 644 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  carbohydrates: 52 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 9 g
author: HelloFresh
---

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Mince the @shallot{1}(minced). Strip the thyme
leaves from the @thyme{1%sprig}, then finely chop. Trim the
@green beans{6%ounce}. Peel and grate the @Idaho potato{1}(peeled and grated),
then season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss the green beans on a #baking sheet{} with 1/2 tablespoon
@olive oil{1/2%tablespoon} and season with salt and pepper. Place the
baking sheet in the oven for about ~{13-15%minutes}, until the green beans are
slightly caramelized.

Meanwhile, place the grated potato in the center of a #kitchen towel{} or
#cheesecloth{} and sprinkle with half the thyme. Working over a #small bowl{},
bring together the corners of the rowel and squeeze as much liquid out of
potatoes as possible.

Heat 2 tablespoons @olive oil{2%tablespoons} in a large #pan{} over medium
heat. Place 2 tablespoon mounds of the potato mixture into the pan and press
with a #spatula{} to flatten. Cook for ~{2-3%minutes} per side, until golden
brown. Season with salt and pepper and set aside.

In the same pan, heat another 1/2 tablespoon @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon} over
medium-high heat. Season the @pork chops{2} on both sides with salt and
pepper, then add to the pan to cook for ~{2-3%minutes} per side, until golden
brown but not cooked through. Remove the baking sheet from the oven, then
transfer the chops and potato cakes to the baking sheet for ~{4-5%minutes},
until pork is just barely pink on the inside and the potato cakes are crisp.
Remove the green beans from baking sheet, if done, and set aside.

Meanwhile, in the same pan, heat @olive oil{1%teaspoon} over medium heat. Add
the shallot and remaining thyme and cook for ~{2%minutes}, until slightly
softened. Add the @Dijon mustard{1%tablespoon}, @water{1/2%cup}, and the
@veggie stock concentrate{1} to the pan and stir to combine. Bring to a
simmer and cook until reduced by half. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice the pork chops against the grain and serve alongside the green beans and
potato cakes. Drizzle with pan sauce and enjoy!

> Wringing out the potatoes is the secret to super crispy potato cakes - if you
> ever made latkes or hashbrowns, you know the drill. Don't forget to season your
> potato cakes while they're still hot!